XXIV THE NEW ECCLESIASTICAL SYSTEM, 1523-4

By 1523 the growth of Lutheran communities had raised the question of the supply of pastors3 the disuse of Private Masses, that of provision for their support; the changes in worship, pro- posed by Carlstadt and resisted by Luther‚ that of liturgical re- adjustment. All three questions now received attention. On 11 March 1523 [No. 63] Luther gave notice of the substitution of weekly for daily Mass (quoted in Rietscliel, Leltrbuclz der Liturgik, i. 398 n. 6).
